The quality really went down for Indian Kitchen. In the past they had the BEST chicken tikka masala. It had the perfect blend of spices.  This past order the chicken tikka masala tasted bland and stale. The chicken pakora tasted frozen and one piece was entirely inedible. It was either a huge chunk of fat or not fully cooked. I couldn’t tell, I just spit it out into a napkin and dared not to look. The poori bread arrived cold and soggy.  Also the restaurant had a coupon for a free soda when you spend over $30. Despite calling and telling the woman on the phone SPECIFICALLY the kind of soda I wanted, the soda still went missing. I had to call again and ask for the soda to be delivered. I feel bad for the delivery guys, but bad management affects everyone.  We will not be ordering from Indian Kitchen again.

It was neon red, and so sweet we couldn’t even think about desert afterwards. Plus, the food coloring stayed on our hands for hours afterwards and got on our clothes even after washing our hands with soap. Garlic naan was also super dry. Please don’t waste your time or money like we did.
